    {
      "id": "js-201-intro",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "nodejs",
      "source": "# JavaScript 201 — Modern ES6+ Features\n\nES6 (ECMAScript 2015) was the biggest update to JavaScript in its history. Every year since, TC39 has shipped new features. This notebook covers the ones you'll use every day.\n\n> **Runtime:** These cells run in Node.js using CommonJS modules (`require` / `module.exports`). No `import`/`export` syntax here.\n\n## What you'll learn\n| Feature | Why it matters |\n|---|---|\n| `let` / `const` | Block scope, no hoisting surprises |\n| Arrow functions | Lexical `this`, concise syntax |\n| Template literals | String interpolation, multi-line |\n| Destructuring | Unpack arrays/objects cleanly |\n| Default, rest, spread | Flexible function signatures |\n| Classes | Prototype-based OOP with clean syntax |\n| Promises + async/await | Tame callback hell |",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
